description.V: *mumbling* What? Who knows what? I know what does, but he dozed unwisely! The Hermit of Awadji knows what's what, but what's left of him is I don't know where. But I do know what the Great Fire Djinn enjoys for lunch...mushroom kebabs! Aahahaha!

minidescription.V: Rescue the Hermit of Awadji from the Caverns of Living Fire. But be wary! He is being held captive by a Great Fire Djinn on Level 30.

completiondescription.V: Thanks to you Awadji has returned along with some of my sanity, but please give him time to recover from the ordeal. Upon returning from your next dungeon expedition, seek him near the obelisk.

incompletedescription.V: Erble Gerble What? I see no Awadji!

description.V: The Kazar'ost's Hearty Military Spear of Quickness, an artifact that has long guarded our fair town, has been lost! Beasts came in the night, and stole it away - I've heard to level 10 of The Caverns of Living Fire. Return it, and you will be rewarded. I'll give you this Ancient Staff as reward!

minidescription.V: Retrieve Kazar'ost's Hearty Military Spear of Quickness from level 10. Your reward is a Ancient Staff.

completiondescription.V:
Thank goodness! You've found the Kazar'ost's Hearty Military Spear of Quickness! And here is your reward. My thanks to you!
You receive 1508 Experience 502 Fame 9681 Gold
Ancient Staff Received

incompletedescription.V: Please return when you have found the Kazar'ost's Hearty Military Spear of Quickness.

name.V: Kazar'ost's Hearty Military Spear of Quickness

description.V: A Antman named Kivildum and its army of Gelloptopuss has stolen a Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar and taken it to level 12 of The Caverns of Living Fire - defeat the rabble, and return the Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar!

minidescription.V: Destroy Kivildum the Antman and its Gelloptopus minions on level 12 and return the Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar.

completiondescription.V:
Thank you for retrieving the Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar from Kivildum and its minions! Here is your reward!
You receive 5419 Experience 1168 Fame 11624 Gold

incompletedescription.V: Please return when you have defeated Kivildum and its minions and found the Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar.

name.V: Eldduruk's Mighty Golden Pirate of the Jaguar

description.V: Yesterday, I sat upon a gilded throne, ruling all that you see as the mighty king of Ekbatan. I speak to you now as nothing more than a lowly beggar. You must lift this curse... if not for me, then for my kingdom. Redeem yourself, and restore our glorious city!

incompletedescription.V: Please return when the task is complete!
